metadata.name: looking through a glass #199
metadata.description:
or life is a colorful mess
or not your usual generative forest

this art project continues the path that 'life is a (beautiful) mess' began with the representation of our lives using drawing lines that make repetitive patterns
as life develops, we look at it through the glass of our unique existence. every event, emotion and thought we experience stain our personal glass and conditions our regard towards the world that surrounds us
the cercles in every composition, represents that glass that we all have between us and the world, and the movement of the lines under it, life developing as we observe it
or it's just another figurative generative art project, as you wish...

10 different palettes
over 30 different color pens
single or multiple color glasses or cercles option
press [1], [2], [3], [4] keys to multiply resolution and reload the piece
press [s] to capture an image .png
press [r] to reload the animation
click the mouse to stop the drawing
doubleclick the mouse to resume the drawing

generative art created by mehno using p5js

metadata.name: Psilocybe Azurescens #25
metadata.description:
Psilocybe Azurescens is a generative algorithm that draws a very potent psychedelic fungus. The Azurescens species occurs naturally along a small area of the West Coast of the United States, including in parts of Oregon and California.  The mushroom has an affinity for coastal dune grasses.

The halftone hatching patterns and 3d mushroom geometries are all unique and driven by fx features and the transaction hash.  

- Double click to enable turntable mode
- Click or touch and drag to rotate in 3D, scroll or pinch to zoom
- Don’t eat too many of these super funky boomerangs off-chain - they are strong!

Created by @capnganj - one love <3

metadata.name: Millefoglie #201
metadata.description:
"A mille-feuille (French pronunciation: ​[mil fœj], "thousand-sheets"), also known by the names Napoleon, vanilla slice, and custard slice, is a dessert made of puff pastry layered with pastry cream. Its modern form was influenced by improvements made by Marie-Antoine Carême.

Traditionally, a mille-feuille is made up of three layers of puff pastry (pâte feuilletée), alternating with two layers of pastry cream (crème pâtissière). The top pastry layer is finished in various ways: sometimes it is topped with whipped cream, or it may be dusted with icing sugar, cocoa, pastry crumbs, or sliced almonds. It may also be glazed with icing or fondant alone, or in alternating white (icing) and brown (chocolate) or other colored icing stripes, and combed to create a marbled effect." — Wikipedia

Prints available upon request: prints@stefancontiero.com
Best enjoyed on browsers supporting Display-P3 color gamut.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

@stefan_contiero

metadata.name: Toccata #374
metadata.description:
Toccata is a piece about decay, about the impermanent. The emergence over time or, rather, progression of entropy is a key characteristic of our universe. Everything evolves to nothing. We as mortal beings have sometimes trouble reconciling with this idea. Humans have sought immortality for millennia, be it through ancient potions or modern medicine, be it from leaving a legacy that we feel will stand the test of time. It will, only to decay later than us.

Toccata is a piece about change. Change lies at the heart of human cognition and human nature. Our thoughts and our emotions happen over time, and are a function of the change that is both around us and at the very core of our selves. Change comes in nature in cycles. Seasons of growth, seasons of ripe fruits of life, seasons of decay, of death, rebirth.

Toccata is music. We find music to convey some of the deepest streams of human condition, connecting it to some other form of being. Music also happens over time, and music happens because of change. Music encodes our feelings better than any other aid we may have. Toccata incorporates this at its very core, as the main sound is Andreas' family piano where he learned to play, sampled this past July.

Read more about the piece, and the collaboration between Marcelo and Andreas on andreasrau.eu/toccata

---

Basic controls:
- Click on the piece or press spacebar to start it (WebAudio requires user intervention for the music to start). Once the music has started, again click or press spacebar to play/pause.
- Press “s” to save a still at the current resolution
- Press “r” to start recording a video at the current resolution, then “r” again to stop.

---

WebM audio-video recording performed using the library RecordRTC by https://muazkhan.com/, MIT licence.

metadata.name: Tuesday #116
metadata.description: Maybe it's inspired by the marks left by coffee cups in my notebook. Maybe the doodles in that same notebook, often squares and circles, somehow influenced this work. Maybe the Bridget Riley book sitting on the shelf above gently whispered to me when I wasn't looking. Or maybe I just played with an idea and found it pleasing. The only thing I'm certain of – it was definitely a Tuesday.

metadata.name: Natt #17
metadata.description:
Natt is a short exploration of a view. On not so recent travels I captured a photo of a small town across a large body of water. It was night and the photograph was blurry, but the emotion stayed with me. It was an emotion of calm and tranquility, accepting the darkness of night and knowing that across the water was a group of people living together, creating a beacon of light. 

Natt is the generative take on this photograph, attempting to capture the same emotion in a purely digital format. 


Press “space” to pause the animation and “s” to save the current view.

For higher resolutions, add “?pd=x” (x being a number >1) to the url when in live view and refresh, then press “s” to save. Note, for higher values of “x” rendering will take longer, start with a low number like 2-3 and work your way up to the desired size. 


Generative artwork by Tengil, 2022.

For licenses see bundle.js.LICENSE.txt.

metadata.name: Twistings #160
metadata.description:
✧ TWISTINGS ✧

Twistings, the "Explore Variety" collection, explores the beauty & variety that is hidden within the simple math of Archimedean spirals.

There are seven different circular "entities", each brought forward by using slightly different mathematical settings of the spiral formulas: Drops, Circles, Fireworks, Flowers, Roses, Spirals & Twisters.

____

✧ CURATED / RANDOM ✧

I love both the concept of a heavily curated set, hand picked by the artist, the best representation / the most beautiful, but also the concept of the larger, random collections showing the variety hidden within the algorithm.

I've therefore also released an "Artist Curated" collection of 7 pieces that I meticulously hand-picked from over 1000 outputs. You can find these on the platform 1stDibs.com/nft (under my name "nadieh"). They represent my favorite for each of the seven unique entities. A free mint of this "Explore Variety" collection will be airdropped to each buyer of a "Curated" piece.

____

✧ OPTIONS ✧

n - Toggle grainy noise on/off (on by default, it's subtle to see)

s - Save the image at the current window size and pixel density

To save a larger image you can add the parameter `&pixeldensity=2` (or another number) to the end of the URL when viewed on the live page. Afterwards press "s" to save the image. The number is the factor with which the width and height are increased w.r.t. the current window size.

-- The larger the image / pixeldensity, the longer it will take to create & save --

____

✧ NOTES ✧

It works best and fastest in Firefox!

As of the drop day there is a browser bug for Chrome on the ARM Apple laptops. It incorrectly visualizes certain color blend modes. The following color palettes are affected: Antique, Camping, Pastel, Prime & Rainbow. I hope/assume this will be fixed soon. 

____

Created by Nadieh Bremer
Twitter & Instagram: @NadiehBremer
Website: VisualCinnamon.com

metadata.name: Crash Euphoria #233
metadata.description:
My first foray into shaders and GLSL: This piece experiments with layering many textures guided by an underlying pattern. Each pixel value dictates which pattern is displayed. There are varying levels of imperfections in each pattern, some choose a single color, some use a color guide pattern, some individual strokes decide on another color altogether. These layers are compiled in a shader and warped.

Press 's' in live view to save a png

Created with p5.js and chroma.js

metadata.name: High Spirits! #7
metadata.description:
There’s always a time and a place to let loose, sit back, and lift those spirits! Through the ages, images of the filled cup, mug, or cocktail glass have molded the way we envision relaxation and good times. They’ve encoded an escape, a panacea, a nostalgic refuge, and a feeling that we seek — but may not find. 

So instead, let’s stay in the moment and live sip by sip, here and now. Let’s look directly into the blazing neon lights, experience something unexpected, and remember that the best drink is one shared. Cheers to all!

--------

Many pieces of High Spirits! match the community-favorite cocktails shared in the Tender Discord’s #happyhour channel… others are timeless cocktails and mocktails, defined in bold headline. Still more outputs are generative mysteries, concocted from Mr. Kislev’s Kode, open to your inventive interpretations. Enjoy the eighties electric vibes and mid-century styling, print a poster, and trade for your favorites!

--------

TENDER x Orr Kislev
September 2022

metadata.name: Ari's Thread #68
metadata.description:
I side with the idea that we made this reality so weird merely to satisfy our -psychotic- need to overcomplicate things. Not you, of course.

That's why I believe that our choices don't "create our own path" but a maze for others to (try to) solve.
This God or that One or none, the old songs or the new ones, rooting for or against…
The deepest we meet into each other's maze, the more choices we share. Reciprocally, when we lack the interest to explore even a couple of turns, we're but a first impression to each other.

This work examines those ideas by continually presenting options to N individuals and then tracking their choices, which in turn generates different outputs at different depths.

To access them:
- press "S" for story mode, the sequence of choices
  - then, press "1" through "5" to change the speed
- press "L" for landscape, the first impression
- press "D" to see the details and view the mazes (may take a while)

metadata.name: Fält #52
metadata.description:
Fält is a study of shape, colour and texture. Designed to bring joy to the viewer, this is a work to light up the darkness of winter and awake feelings of curiosity. 

The series is controlled by a large number of random processes, from recursive subdivision with tweaks through Chaikin smoothing of the resulting polygons to mild domain warping of the entire canvas. Finally each shape is filled using small shapes, creating a warm and soft feel. 

Some features are tracked, but many are hidden in the resulting visuals, which will make exploration of the final collection surprising and rewarding.
